The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 No Korean decision yet

Seoul: North and South Korea have not yet agreed on fielding a joint Olympic team because Seoul wants selection on ability and Pyongyang seeks equal representation, sports officials said on Thursday. 

While we want a merit-based system, North Koreans want an equal representation in forming a single team, said (South) Korea Olympic Committee spokesman Kim Tae-hyung. (AFP) 




